{"type":"message","id":"881dfc49","parentId":"158da370","timestamp":"2026-04-14T01:42:57.479Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pd4wud950lmi_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import dotenv from 'dotenv';\ndotenv.config();\n\nimport { DatabaseAdapter } from './common/infrastructure/database.adapter';\nimport { initSystemAdmin2Account, initBuiltInRoles } from './migration/initSeedData';\nimport { rolesService } from './modules/roles/roles.service';\nimport { UserRoleDefined } from './modules/userRoles/userRoles.interface';\nimport logger from './common/logger';\n\nasync function seed() {\n    try {\n        const databaseAdapter = new DatabaseAdapter();\n        await databaseAdapter.connect();\n        logger.info('Connected to database, checking/seeding admin2...');\n\n        // Ensure roles exist and get admin role id\n        await initBuiltInRoles();\n        const adminRole = await rolesService.getRoleByName(UserRoleDefined.Admin);\n\n        if (adminRole) {\n            await initSystemAdmin2Account(adminRole.id);\n            logger.info('Admin2 account check/seed completed!');\n        } else {\n            logger.error('Admin role not found!');\n        }\n\n        // Small delay to ensure all logs are written\n        setTimeout(() => process.exit(0), 1000);\n    } catch (error) {\n        logger.error('Seeding failed:', error);\n        process.exit(1);\n    }\n}\n\nseed();"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":30,"aggregated":"import dotenv from 'dotenv';\ndotenv.config();\n\nimport { DatabaseAdapter } from './common/infrastructure/database.adapter';\nimport { initSystemAdmin2Account, initBuiltInRoles } from './migration/initSeedData';\nimport { rolesService } from './modules/roles/roles.service';\nimport { UserRoleDefined } from './modules/userRoles/userRoles.interface';\nimport logger from './common/logger';\n\nasync function seed() {\n    try {\n        const databaseAdapter = new DatabaseAdapter();\n        await databaseAdapter.connect();\n        logger.info('Connected to database, checking/seeding admin2...');\n\n        // Ensure roles exist and get admin role id\n        await initBuiltInRoles();\n        const adminRole = await rolesService.getRoleByName(UserRoleDefined.Admin);\n\n        if (adminRole) {\n            await initSystemAdmin2Account(adminRole.id);\n            logger.info('Admin2 account check/seed completed!');\n        } else {\n            logger.error('Admin role not found!');\n        }\n\n        // Small delay to ensure all logs are written\n        setTimeout(() => process.exit(0), 1000);\n    } catch (error) {\n        logger.error('Seeding failed:', error);\n        process.exit(1);\n    }\n}\n\nseed();","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776130977321}}
{"type":"message","id":"1614a371","parentId":"881dfc49","timestamp":"2026-04-14T01:43:13.805Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, there's a seed.ts that creates admin account. Now I have everything I need. Let me spawn the agents:\n\n1. `senior-backend` - to start the server, seed data, and test each module's API endpoints\n2. `realistic-seeder` - to add realistic seed data for each module (but the seed.ts only seeds admin, so realistic-seeder might not apply here since it seems to only seed admin)\n\nActually, looking at the seed.ts, it only creates admin account. The realistic-seeder agent might be overkill since there's no comprehensive seeder. Let me just spawn `senior-backend` to:\n\n\n1. Start the BE server\n2. Seed admin data\n3. Test each module's API\n\nNow I'll define the 5 modules to test: auth (public), system, education, operation, and notification (all protected). Let me spawn senior-backend with clear instructions.","thinkingSignature":"3e85f6178715829b76718daf78a4c3c30401657b48a14c88e148c4613e10bd4f"},{"type":"text","text":"Có 5 module cần test. Spawn `senior-backend` để start server, seed data và test API.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_u7k1xvgznldw_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"You are senior-backend. Test all 5 API modules for ahv-dtlx-backend.\n\n## Context\n- Workspace: /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend\n- Branch: feature/clean-architecture-migration\n- Server port: 5555 (from .env.example)\n- 5 modules: auth (public), system, education, operation, notification (all protected except auth)\n- Label: dtlx:api-test\n\n## Steps\n\n### 1. Setup & Start\n- cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend\n- Check .env exists (cp .env.example .env if missing)\n- Run: yarn seed  (seeds admin account)\n- Start server: yarn dev  (runs on port 5555)\n- Wait for \"listening\" / \"started\" in logs\n- Get server URL: http://localhost:5555\n\n### 2. Seed realistic data\n- Create realistic test data for each module:\n  * Education: courses, classes, subjects\n  * Operation: vehicles, schedules\n  * Notification: announcements\n- Use POST requests to seed via API\n\n### 3. Test APIs module by module\n\n**AUTH (public):**\n- POST /api/v1/auth/login → get JWT token\n- Store token for protected requests\n\n**SYSTEM (protected - requires Bearer token):**\n- GET /api/v1/system/users\n- GET /api/v1/system/roles\n\n**EDUCATION (protected):**\n- GET /api/v1/education/courses\n- POST /api/v1/education/courses\n- GET /api/v1/education/classes\n- GET /api/v1/education/subjects\n\n**OPERATION (protected):**\n- GET /api/v1/operation/vehicles\n- GET /api/v1/operation/schedules\n\n**NOTIFICATION (protected):**\n- GET /api/v1/notification\n- POST /api/v1/notification\n\n### 4. Report\nFor EACH endpoint tested, report:\n- ✅ /path — status code, response summary\n- ❌ /path — status code, error message\n\nUse curl or node fetch to test. Start server in background.\n\n## Rules\n- NEVER push any code\n- NEVER commit anything\n- Read-only API testing only\n- Report ALL results clearly","label":"dtlx:api-test","runtime":"subagent","agentId":"senior-backend","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend","runTimeoutSeconds":600,"mode":"run","cleanup":"delete"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":374,"output":839,"cacheRead":88613,"cacheWrite":189,"totalTokens":90015,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776130977493,"responseId":"062ccea2e668afe63ca892136e3bc0a3"}}
