{"type":"message","id":"92a2e6b3","parentId":"b176aa52","timestamp":"2026-04-14T02:48:22.324Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to understand the pattern of errors:\n\n1. Controllers return `.data.docs` but interfaces expect `.data` (for single) or different structure\n2. Services return `{ data, meta }` but interfaces expect `{ data: { docs }, meta }` or vice versa\n\nLet me check the actual controller/service patterns vs interface patterns.\n\nThe interface `IListResponse<T>` expects:\n```ts\n{\n  status?: string;\n  data: {\n    docs: T[];  // <-- nested under data.docs\n  };\n  meta: IMeta;\n  message?: string;\n}\n```\n\nBut services are returning:\n\n\n```ts\n{ data: T[], meta: IMeta }  // flat, no data.docs nesting\n```\n\nSo the fix is either:\n- Option A: Change interfaces to match what services return (flat `{ data, meta }`)\n- Option B: Change services to wrap in `{ data: { docs } }`\n\nSince the clean architecture migration seems to have changed the interfaces but not updated all services/controllers, I should fix the interfaces to match what the code currently returns — that's the minimal change approach.\n\nBut wait, `IResponse<T>` is also wrong — it has `data: { doc: T }` which doesn't align with the actual service returns. Let me look at what services are actually returning to understand the real pattern.","thinkingSignature":"2d23c72f35000560002d9165bdb35f50c131f56a8186c2d351ec60e94ec11ace"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uuv4nqn04meo_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend && grep -n \"return {\" src/modules/coursesStudents/coursesStudents.service.ts | grep -E \"data:|meta:|docs:\" | head -5"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":348,"output":358,"cacheRead":108567,"cacheWrite":437,"totalTokens":109710,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0