{"type":"message","id":"c5e7e668","parentId":"03d4be56","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:38:13.456Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The roles don't exist. The `initBuiltInRoles()` is trying to find the admin role but it doesn't exist. Let me check `initSeedData.ts`:","thinkingSignature":"b3a98138b5dafe8be24f38f73db3471b0586ae99cf3e007410a8235ea5e2d669"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gfahspl6dx2m_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces/ahv-driving-training-system/ahv-dtlx-backend && cat src/migration/initSeedData.ts | grep -A20 \"initBuiltInRoles\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":745,"output":99,"cacheRead":73668,"cacheWrite":213,"totalTokens":74725,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776137887068,"responseId":"062ce9a0da140ef22f7306ed7532e686"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9b890eb1","parentId":"c5e7e668","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:38:14.090Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gfahspl6dx2m_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"export async function initBuiltInRoles(): Promise<IRolesResponse[]> {\n    // check if existed\n    const result: IRolesResponse[] = [];\n    for (const role of BuiltInRoleSeeds) {\n        const existed = await rolesService.getRoleByName(role.role_name);\n        if (existed) {\n            result.push(existed);\n            continue;\n        }\n        // create new\n        const record = await rolesService.createRole(role);\n        result.push(record);\n    }\n    return result;\n}\n\nexport async function initSystemAdminAccount(adminRoleId: string): Promise<IUserResponse> {\n    // check if it existed\n    const existedAdminUsers = await userRolesService.getUsersByRoleId(adminRoleId);\n    if (existedAdminUsers.length > 0) return await userService.getUserById(existedAdminUsers[0].user_id);\n    // create new"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":316,"aggregated":"export async function initBuiltInRoles(): Promise<IRolesResponse[]> {\n    // check if existed\n    const result: IRolesResponse[] = [];\n    for (const role of BuiltInRoleSeeds) {\n        const existed = await rolesService.getRoleByName(role.role_name);\n        if (existed) {\n            result.push(existed);\n            continue;\n        }\n        // create new\n        const record = await rolesService.createRole(role);\n        result.push(record);\n    }\n    return result;\n}\n\nexport async function initSystemAdminAccount(adminRoleId: string): Promise<IUserResponse> {\n    // check if it existed\n    const existedAdminUsers = await userRolesService.getUsersByRoleId(adminRoleId);\n    if (existedAdminUsers.length > 0) return await userService.getUserById(existedAdminUsers[0].user_id);\n    // create new","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776137894080}}
{"type":"message","id":"f040bc1c","parentId":"9b890eb1","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:38:28.579Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `initBuiltInRoles` function iterates through `BuiltInRoleSeeds` and for each role, tries to get it by name. If it doesn't exist, it creates it. But the error says \"Không tìm thấy vai trò 'admin'\" - this means the `rolesService.getRoleByName('admin')` returns null.\n\nBut the roles collection is empty (no roles). Let me check why `rolesService.getRoleByName` is throwing an error instead of returning null:\n\n```typescript\nasync getRoleByName(roleName: string): Promise<IRolesResponse | null> {\n    const role = await Roles.findOne({ role_name: roleName });\n    if (!role) {\n        logger.warn(`[RolesService] getRoleByName: Không tìm thấy vai trò \"${roleName}\"`);\n        return null;  // ← returns null\n    }\n    return role.transform();\n}\n```\n\nSo the service returns null when the role isn't found. The problem is in `initSeedData.ts` at line 26 where `getRoleByName` is called - it's likely not handling the null return properly and throwing an error instead.\n\nActually, looking at the code, `getRoleByName` returns null gracefully, but then the next line tries to access `adminRole.id` on a null value. That's the actual issue - the null check isn't happening before accessing the role's properties.\n\nThe real problem is that `initBuiltInRoles()` fails when it can't find an existing admin role, so the seed process never completes. I should either manually seed the roles first, or just create an admin user directly since we know the credentials needed.\n\nLet me try manually inserting the admin role and user directly into the database.","thinkingSignature":"1d142122407483c13cfcc9924aebecf2dfe02a20017567abd56cb0218ac51497"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d9jx1qz4478p_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mongosh \"mongodb://localhost:27017/dtlx\" --quiet --eval \"\ndb.roles.insertOn