{"type":"message","id":"0b4c1256","parentId":"9d672059","timestamp":"2026-04-14T03:39:09.343Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It found the admin role but failed on the 'sale' role. The issue is that `initBuiltInRoles` loops through `BuiltInRoleSeeds` and for each role, it calls `getRoleByName` - if the role doesn't exist, it should create it, but `getRoleByName` throws an error when it doesn't find the role (instead of returning null).\n\nWait no - looking at the service code, `getRoleByName` logs a warning and returns `null` when not found. But the error says \"Không tìm thấy thông tin vai trò này trên hệ thống\" - this is thrown in `initSeedData.ts`:\n\n\nThe function tries to get a role by name, logs a warning if it's not found, then throws an error if the result is null. So the real problem is that `BuiltInRoleSeeds` includes a 'sale' role that doesn't exist yet, and the code is configured to fail rather than create missing roles. Let me check what roles are actually defined in the seeds and whether there's a way to handle this more gracefully, or if I should just create the missing role directly in the database.","thinkingSignature":"51a6d7433a1c41f2ca9d6e2e2ba86f58e6a047a35001471f70eac768317a3d5a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ytg4mk5k1hsu_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"mongosh \"mongodb://localhost:27017/dtlx\" --quiet --eval \"\nconst seeds = [\n  { role_name: 'sale', description: 'Sale', permissions: [] },\n  { role_name: 'teacher', description: 'Giáo viên', permissions: [] },\n  { role_name: 'student', description: 'Học viên', permissions: [] },\n  { role_name: 'staff', description: 'Nhân viên', permissions: [] },\n];\nseeds.forEach(r => {\n  db.roles.updateOne({ role_name: r.role_name }, { \\$set: { ...r, created_at: new Date(), updated_at: new Date() } }, { upsert: true });\n});\nprint('Roles seeded');\n\" 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-D